OL,6,F"The screams and groans of Mr Shah
OL,7,Ffell silent, shortly before the
OL,8,Fdefendant walked away from the
OL,9,Fmutilated and lifeless body."
OL,11,FThe other wounded man ran back to the
OL,12,FB&B shouting 'the old man has been
OL,13,Fstabbed' and the emergency services
OL,14,Fwere called but Mr Shah was pronounced
OL,15,Fdead at the scene.
OL,17,FLenaghan walked back to his
OL,18,Faccommodation and was described as
OL,19,F"calm but out of it... like he had
OL,20,Fsnapped."
